<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="166" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,356,1014,1040]" box="[151,356,1014,1040]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,356,1014,1040]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,356,1014,1040]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">
<taxonomicName box="[151,291,1014,1040]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,291,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Cercosaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 1
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1085,1326]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,398,1085,1110]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[405,536,1086,1109]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[405,536,1086,1109]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Cercosaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 1 differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[814,945,1086,1109]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[814,945,1086,1109]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Cercosaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in some aspects of scutellation and color pattern. It is under study as part of the revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[889,1020,1122,1145]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[889,1020,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Cercosaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="166" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1085,1326]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,506,1157,1182]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[517,648,1158,1181]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[517,648,1158,1181]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Cercosaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 1 is endemic to southern Brazilian 
<taxonomicName box="[1122,1240,1157,1182]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="15" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
, where it occurs between the Curuá/Iriri and Purus rivers (
<figureCitation box="[623,708,1193,1218]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1571,1593]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,313,1540]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,303,1549]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Distribution of examined material of Cercosaura sp. 1, Colobosaura modesta, and Gymnophthalmus underwoodi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/581985/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). It is known from the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[1073,1126,1194,1218]" country="Suriname" name="Para" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Pará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1138,1259,1194,1218]" country="Venezuela" name="Amazonas" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1271,1383,1193,1218]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[151,302,1230,1254]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[314,445,1230,1253]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[314,445,1230,1253]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Cercosaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 1 is terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits primary and secondary terra firme forests, and disturbed areas near forest edges, where it is mainly found on the ground (Macedo 
<emphasis box="[1101,1158,1265,1290]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">et al.</emphasis>
2008—referred to as 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="ocellata" subSpecies="bassleri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">C. ocellata bassleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<collectionCode box="[351,429,1302,1326]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/90vz-swjg" name="Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">MPEG</collectionCode>
data).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
